DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

$n = random(2,7,1);


TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Consider the function \(\displaystyle f(x) = \frac{\ln(x)}{x^{$n}}  \).
For this function there are two important numbers \(A<B\) which are either critical
or outside the domain of \(f(x)\):
$BR
\( A = \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = 0;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( B = \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = exp(1/$n);
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
For each of the following intervals, tell whether \( f'(x) \)
is positive (type in \(+\)) or negative (type in \(-\)).
$BR
 \( (A, B) \):
 \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "+";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( (B,\infty) \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "-";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));

BEGIN_TEXT
$BR
Thus we conclude that \(f(x)\) has a local \{ans_rule()\} at \(B\) (type in
MAX or MIN).
END_TEXT
ANS(str_cmp("MAX"));


ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
